\begin_body

\begin_layout Standard
Hang Qian
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
CSC630- Interactive Computer Graphic
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assignment 3
\end_layout

\begin_layout Title
Spaceship
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this assignment I implement a motion simulator for a pair of objects
 (space ships) flying amidst a collection of colored spherical objects (clouds).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The ships are controlled through input from the keyboard.
 Each ship is drawn as a union of a vertical torus and a horizontal torus.
 Torus is a geometric shape that resembles a donut.
 Each ship is associated with a translational velocity (in distance/unittime)
 and a rotational velocity (in degrees/unittime).
 The viewer is positioned in one of these space ships.
 By clicking left mouse button, the program switches the viewpoint from
 one space ship to the other (i.e.
 you beam yourself to the other ship).
 When sitting in one space ship, you can observe the other ship as it moves.
 In addition to the ships, there are a collection of spherical clouds and
 a large square patch which forms the ground over which ships are flying.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Instruction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Left mouse button: switch between two space ships.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Middle mouse button: pause and resume the game.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Right mouse button: move one step and output all information to standard
 output.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
'a': speed up the heading velocity of current ship.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
's': slow down the heading velocity of current ship.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
'l': speed up the spinning velocity of current ship.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
'k': slow down the spinning velocity of current ship.
\end_layout

\end_body
